      "content": "exactly. it's just a heavy cycle of wanting, needing, and suffering, and for what? to leave a footprint that won't even be there for a second in cosmic time. if the end is always nothingness, then why carry the weight of existing? doesn't it seem more peaceful to just exit early instead of waiting for the slow decay? it feels like the only way to actually win against the void is to choose it on your own terms.",
